         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">N. M. ¶  24/8/71 ¶  ¶ Many thanks for your kind note ¶  &amp; the memoir &amp; specimens which will be placed in the Museum. ¶  ¶ I have just got the £20 for Maxwell ¶  / £15 first ordered &amp; received &amp; £5 ord...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.08.24b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Frederick McCoy</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Director’s letterbooks, MVS 2/1 3, p. 455, Melbourne Museum.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">N. M.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>National Museum.</p>
               </note> 24/8/71</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">My dear Dr von Müeller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many thanks for your kind note<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
               </note> &amp; the memoir &amp; specimens which will be placed in the Museum.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have just got the £20 for Maxwell<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See F. McCoy to M, 12 June 1871 (in this edition as 71-06-12a), and M to F. McCoy, 14 June 1871.</p>
               </note> / £15 first ordered &amp; received &amp; £5 ordered by you since, to arrive/. Would you kindly cause him to return the voucher by next mail signed and witnessed &amp; if you have no objection, sign me the temporary one to enable me to receive another advance of money for other claimants.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever My dear Dr. Mueller &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>F. McC.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I congratulate you on your triumph.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>It had been announced in Parliament on 23 August 1871 that arrangements would be made to 'transfer Mr Ferguson to the Lands Department as promptly as possible' (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 24 August 1871, p. 6). William Ferguson, Inspector of Forests, had been placed in the Botanic Gardens to oversee the horticultural aspects, but M and he were at loggerheads from the moment the appointment was made.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr von Müeller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Botanic G.</p>
